Police have found the bodies of two males in the Dube hostel. JOHANNESBURG Soweto police have confirmed two bodies have been found at the Dube Hostel.A community member on Wednesday found the body of a 30-year-old man who died from a gunshot wound.Police say the motive of the murder is unknown.The police's Nomvula Mbense says another man was also found in a vacant flat in the hostel. They found that he hanged himself there, but he is known by the family because he lived in Zone 5. 